  "text": "Ablating miR-155 control of AID expression led to increased protein expression in switching cells, which undergo significantly higher levels of CSR. It also led to increased protein expression in germinal-center cells. However, increased AID expression did not lead to more SHM in the Ig locus, in accordance with previous work by the Honjo group [CITATION_1] , whose members have shown that transgenic AID overexpression does not lead to an increase in SHM. Our data presented here, and the data published by Muto et al., support the notion of the existence of a limiting factor that targets AID to the Ig locus so that, in its presence, excess AID cannot access the locus (though in its absence it can, possibly in a stochastic fashion).",
